using UnityEngine;

public class ParticleError : MonoBehaviour
{
    public ParticleSystem particles;

    void Start()
    {
        // Forgot to check if particles is null
        particles.Play();  // NullReferenceException!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
You're trying to use a ParticleSystem that was never assigned.

**The fix:**
```csharp
void Start()
{
    if (particles != null)
    {
        particles.Play();
    }
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check if ParticleSystem is assigned before using it."
